# Counting Sort

## Problem

Counting Sort is a non-comparison sorting algorithm used to sort integers by counting the frequency of each element.

It works efficiently when the range of elements is small.

---

# Algorithm / Pseudo Code

BEGIN

INPUT array A
INPUT n

FIND maximum element max

CREATE count array of size max + 1

// Store frequency of elements
FOR i = 0 TO n-1

    count[A[i]] = count[A[i]] + 1

ENDFOR

// Store sorted elements
INITIALIZE index = 0

FOR i = 0 TO max

    WHILE count[i] > 0

        A[index] = i
        index = index + 1

        count[i] = count[i] - 1

    ENDWHILE

ENDFOR

PRINT sorted array

END

---

# Time Complexity

| Case       | Complexity |
| ---------- | ---------- |
| Best Case  | O(n + k)   |
| Worst Case | O(n + k)   |

Where:

* n = number of elements
* k = range of elements

---

# Space Complexity
O(k)

---

# Important Points

* Non-comparison sorting algorithm.
* Works only for integers.
* Efficient for small range values.
* Stable sorting algorithm.
* Faster than comparison sorts for limited range data.
